school_name: New York University- School of Social Work
comments: I took this professor a few years ago for HB and then again for a Practice class. I liked her both times. The Practice class was more fun and there was more time for case discussion. I would recommend her.

school_name: New York University- School of Social Work
comments: Not sure about the other comments but I really liked this professor. I didn\'t think she read her notes at all. I thought the class - Clinical Practice with Children was great. She allowed for some good discussion.

school_name: New York University- School of Social Work
comments: horrible. reads notes, which are a re-tread of assignments. dull. uninspiring. how is she teaching here. might be ok for undergrads but not for grad school.

school_name: New York University- School of Social Work
comments: She reads from her notes and very poor presentation skills. Class was very boring. She grades fairly and helpful

school_name: New York University- School of Social Work
comments: I thought this teacher was very accommodating and willing to answer questions. She was very knowledgeable about the subject and I felt like I learned a lot in her class

school_name: New York University- School of Social Work
New York University- School of Social Work
comments: Pathetic to have paid so much money for NYU and end up with such a lame professor. As stated, all she does is read of a list of notes. I am totally unprepared for HB2, whatever you do, do not take this professor. I wish someone had let me know how awful this would be. She may be okay for an undergrad class, but not here!!!

school_name: New York University- School of Social Work
comments: Liked her. She was very nice and supportive. Thought she was interesting and smart and liked her class. Would recommend!

school_name: New York University- School of Social Work
comments: she\'s very nice and is open to answering questions, and helpful. she\'s very into letting the class give their input which sometimes is annoying because you don\'t really get to hear about her view and experience. but, in sum - good class.

school_name: New York University- School of Social Work
comments: This teacher is awful, i wish someone had warned me against her. She reads her notes instead of teaching, she doesn\'t add anything to the readings, her midterm and final are completely unclear and your grade suffers because of it. She also doesn\'t seem to know anything more than the average masters student, I have no idea how she got this job.

school_name: New York University- School of Social Work
comments: She is very nice, but does not stray from her notes that come straight from the reading/textbook. Very dry presentation. You can get the same info from just reading.
